<h2 class="sec-h2">Questions international sellers ask</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Do I need a Ukrainian legal entity to start?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>No. For your test launch, we process shipments under our entity. This lets you validate the market with zero bureaucracy. When you're ready to scale, we connect you with legal partners who register a Ukrainian FOP or LLC in 2-3 weeks. Sellers from Turkey, EU, US, and UK use this approach.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How do I get my products to your warehouse?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Most international sellers ship via courier (DHL, FedEx, UPS) to our address near Boryspil Airport, Kyiv Oblast. Some use freight forwarders for larger volumes. We handle customs-cleared goods &mdash; once your shipment arrives, we unload, inspect, barcode, and shelve within 24 hours.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Does your team speak English?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Dedicated English-speaking account managers. Dashboard, inventory reports, and shipping notifications are all in English. We communicate via email, Telegram, WhatsApp, or Zoom &mdash; whatever works best for you.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">What if there's a power outage?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Our warehouses have 3 industrial diesel generators, 2 fiber-optic internet providers, and Starlink satellite backup. Since February 2022, we've had zero days of downtime &mdash; even during the most severe nationwide blackouts. Your orders ship on time, every single day.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How do returns work?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>When a buyer returns a product via Nova Poshta, we receive it at our warehouse, inspect the condition (with photo documentation per your guidelines), and either restock the item or set it aside. You see everything in your dashboard in real-time.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Can I sell on multiple marketplaces at once?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes &mdash; that's our specialty. One warehouse, one inventory pool. Orders from Rozetka, Prom.ua, Kasta, OLX, and others are all fulfilled from the same stock. Inventory syncs in real-time across all platforms &mdash; zero risk of overselling.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">What's the minimum to start?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>5,000 UAH/month (~$125). This covers your WMS access, packing materials, labels, and fulfillment services. There's no minimum order volume &mdash; even 5 orders per day works. The per-order cost simply adjusts based on your volume tier.</p></div></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- SEO ARTICLE — unique to EN -->
<section class="article-section">
<div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">GUIDE</div>
<h2>How to sell on Ukrainian marketplaces as a foreign business</h2>
<div class="article-content">
<h3>The opportunity: Ukraine's marketplace landscape</h3>
<p>Ukraine's e-commerce market surpassed $8 billion in 2024-2025. The country has 37+ million active internet users and a rapidly digitizing economy. Unlike mature Western markets where Amazon and eBay dominate, Ukraine has its own ecosystem of marketplaces: Rozetka (the "Amazon of Ukraine" with 30M monthly visits), Prom.ua (40M visits, 100M+ product listings), and OLX (60M visits, the largest classified platform). For international sellers, this represents a massive, underserved market with minimal foreign competition.</p>

<h3>The barrier &mdash; and how to bypass it</h3>
<p>Traditionally, selling on Ukrainian marketplaces required a local legal entity (FOP or LLC), a Ukrainian bank account, a warehouse, local staff, and a working knowledge of Nova Poshta's logistics system. This kept most international sellers out. A fulfillment partner eliminates every one of these barriers. You ship your inventory to a warehouse near Kyiv. The partner integrates with marketplaces via API, processes orders automatically, packs and ships to buyers across Ukraine. You manage everything remotely through an English-language dashboard.</p>

<h3>Starting without a local entity</h3>
<p>The most common question from international sellers: "Do I need to register a company in Ukraine?" The answer is no &mdash; not to start. Modern fulfillment operators can process your initial shipments under their entity, letting you test the market with zero paperwork. Ship a batch of products, list them on Rozetka or Prom.ua, and see what sells. When volumes justify it (typically 50+ orders/day), you register a Ukrainian FOP &mdash; a straightforward process that takes 2-3 weeks with a local legal partner.</p>

<h3>The economics: what it actually costs</h3>
<p>The numbers surprise most international sellers. Order fulfillment starts at 18 UAH (~$0.45) per order for 200+ daily orders. Storage costs 650 UAH (~$15) per cubic meter per month. The minimum monthly commitment is 5,000 UAH (~$125). Compare this to setting up your own operation: warehouse lease ($400+/mo), a single warehouse worker ($500+/mo), WMS software ($100+/mo), power backup, internet &mdash; easily $2,000+/month before you ship a single order. With a fulfillment partner, you pay only for what you use.</p>

<h3>Resilience: the power outage question</h3>
<p>Every international seller asks about Ukraine's infrastructure reliability. It's a valid concern &mdash; and it's one that professional fulfillment operators have solved. MTP Group's warehouses are equipped with 3 industrial diesel generators, dual fiber-optic internet connections, and Starlink satellite backup. Since February 2022, the facility has maintained zero days of downtime. Orders are processed and shipped every single day, regardless of the national grid status. For marketplace sellers, this is critical: a single day of delayed shipments can damage your seller rating for weeks.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

